ENTRY       EC 1.5.1.18                 Enzyme
NAME        ephedrine dehydrogenase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     (-)-ephedrine:NAD+ 2-oxidoreductase
REACTION    (-)-ephedrine + NAD+ = (R)-2-methylimino-1-phenylpropan-1-ol + NADH + H+ [RN:R03614]
ALL_REAC    R03614
SUBSTRATE   (-)-ephedrine [CPD:C01575];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003]
PRODUCT     (R)-2-methylimino-1-phenylpropan-1-ol [CPD:C04351];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The product immediately hydrolyses to methylamine and 1-hydroxy-1-phenylpropan-2-one. Acts on a number of related compounds including (-)-sympatol, (+)-pseudoephedrine and (+)-norephedrine.
HISTORY     EC 1.5.1.18 created 1984
